---
// Standalone page — self-contained styles and scripts, no global.css
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Maryland Glock Ban (SB 334) | Bearing Freedom</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Maryland SB 334 bans Glocks and cruciform trigger bar pistols. Full breakdown of what's banned, who's affected, penalties, and legal challenges."
    />
    <meta
      property="og:title"
      content="Maryland Glock Ban (SB 334) | Bearing Freedom"
    />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Maryland bans Glocks by targeting the cruciform trigger bar. Full breakdown of SB 334 — what's banned, timeline, penalties, and the Bruen problem."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta
      property="og:url"
      content="https://bearingfreedom.com/marylandglockban"
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <!-- GA4 -->
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-YJWJPMSXN4"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag() {
        dataLayer.push(arguments);
      }
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', 'G-YJWJPMSXN4');
    </script>
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oswald:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style is:global>
      *,
      *::before,
      *::after {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }
      :root {
        --bg: #08090c;
        --surface: #10121a;
        --card: #161a24;
        --card-hover: #1c2030;
        --accent: #4a7cff;
        --accent-bright: #6b9aff;
        --accent-dim: rgba(74, 124, 255, 0.1);
        --red: #dc2626;
        --red-dim: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.08);
        --green: #22c55e;
        --green-dim: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.08);
        --yellow: #eab308;
        --yellow-dim: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.08);
        --white: #e8eaf0;
        --light: #c4c8d4;
        --dim: #8890a4;
        --muted: #5a6278;
        --faint: #2e3448;
        --border: #232838;
        --font: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
        --head: 'Oswald', sans-serif;
        --mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      }
      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }
      body {
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--white);
        font-family: var(--font);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      a:hover {
        color: var(--accent-bright);
      }

      /* Nav */
      .nav {
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 50;
        background: rgba(8, 9, 12, 0.92);
        backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding: 0 20px;
      }
      .nav-inner {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        height: 52px;
      }
      .nav-brand {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-weight: 800;
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 18px;
        align-items: center;
      }
      .nav-links a {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 500;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--dim);
      }
      .nav-links a:hover {
        color: var(--white);
      }

      /* Ticker */
      .ticker-bar {
        background: var(--red);
        overflow: hidden;
        white-space: nowrap;
        padding: 6px 0;
      }
      .ticker-label {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 11px;
        background: #000;
        color: #fff;
        padding: 2px 10px;
        margin-right: 12px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      }
      .ticker-text {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #fff;
        letter-spacing: 0.03em;
        animation: tickerScroll 40s linear infinite;
      }
      @keyframes tickerScroll {
        0% {
          transform: translateX(0);
        }
        100% {
          transform: translateX(-50%);
        }
      }

      /* Hero */
      .hero {
        padding: 64px 20px 48px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .hero-inner {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .hero-state {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--accent);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .hero h1 {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: clamp(32px, 6vw, 56px);
        font-weight: 800;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        line-height: 1.05;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .hero-sub {
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--light);
        max-width: 640px;
        line-height: 1.65;
      }
      .hero-meta {
        margin-top: 24px;
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 12px;
      }
      .meta-chip {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
        padding: 5px 12px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--dim);
      }
      .meta-chip.pending {
        border-color: var(--yellow);
        color: var(--yellow);
      }
      .meta-chip.passed {
        border-color: var(--red);
        color: var(--red);
      }

      /* Stats */
      .stats {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));
        gap: 1px;
        background: var(--border);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        margin: 32px auto;
        max-width: 900px;
      }
      .stat {
        background: var(--surface);
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .stat-val {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 28px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--white);
      }
      .stat-val.red {
        color: var(--red);
      }
      .stat-val.yellow {
        color: var(--yellow);
      }
      .stat-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 9px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-top: 6px;
      }

      /* Content sections */
      .content {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 20px;
      }
      .section {
        padding: 48px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .sh {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        color: var(--white);
      }
      .sh::before {
        content: '';
        display: inline-block;
        width: 4px;
        height: 20px;
        background: var(--accent);
        margin-right: 12px;
        vertical-align: middle;
      }
      p {
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        color: var(--light);
        font-size: 16px;
      }

      /* Callout */
      .co {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
        background: var(--accent-dim);
        padding: 16px 20px;
        margin: 20px 0;
        border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      }
      .co-red {
        border-color: var(--red);
        background: var(--red-dim);
      }
      .co-yellow {
        border-color: var(--yellow);
        background: var(--yellow-dim);
      }
      .co-green {
        border-color: var(--green);
        background: var(--green-dim);
      }
      .co-t {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        color: var(--white);
      }
      .co p,
      .co span {
        font-size: 14px;
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      /* Table */
      .tb {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 20px 0;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      .tb th {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        text-align: left;
        padding: 10px 14px;
        background: var(--surface);
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--dim);
      }
      .tb td {
        padding: 10px 14px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--light);
        vertical-align: top;
      }
      .b-ban {
        color: var(--red);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .b-ok {
        color: var(--green);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .b-warn {
        color: var(--yellow);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* Feature list */
      .fl {
        margin: 16px 0;
      }
      .fl-i {
        display: flex;
        align-items: flex-start;
        gap: 10px;
        padding: 8px 0;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--light);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .fl-b {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 8px;
        height: 8px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: var(--red);
        margin-top: 7px;
      }

      /* Timeline */
      .tl {
        margin: 20px 0;
      }
      .tl-item {
        display: flex;
        gap: 16px;
        padding: 12px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      .tl-date {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--dim);
        min-width: 100px;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .tl-text {
        color: var(--light);
      }
      .tl-text.major {
        color: var(--white);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* CTA */
      .cta {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 48px 20px;
      }
      .cta-t {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--dim);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .sub-btn {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 700;
        padding: 12px 28px;
        background: var(--accent);
        color: #fff;
        border-radius: 4px;
        text-decoration: none;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      }
      .sub-btn:hover {
        background: var(--accent-bright);
        color: #fff;
      }

      /* Footer */
      .foot {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding: 24px 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .foot p {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0;
      }

      /* Video */
      .video-embed {
        position: relative;
        padding-bottom: 56.25%;
        margin: 24px 0;
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 4px;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .video-embed iframe {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        border: 0;
      }

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .hero {
          padding: 40px 16px 32px;
        }
        .stats {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        }
        .nav-links {
          display: none;
        }
        .section {
          padding: 32px 0;
        }
        .tl-item {
          flex-direction: column;
          gap: 4px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Nav -->
    <nav class="nav">
      <div class="nav-inner">
        <a href="/" class="nav-brand">BF</a>
        <div class="nav-links">
          <a href="/">Articles</a>
          <a href="/extras">Extras</a>
          <a href="/legislation">VA Tracker</a>
          <a
            href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCmuwdcAbeBR16b8q6CBUsTw"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener">YouTube</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Ticker -->
    <div class="ticker-bar">
      <span class="ticker-label">Breaking</span>
      <span class="ticker-text">
        SB 334 PASSES MARYLAND LEGISLATURE 92-39 &mdash; BANS SALE OF GLOCKS AND
        ALL CRUCIFORM TRIGGER BAR PISTOLS &mdash; ON GOVERNOR MOORE'S DESK
        &mdash; MARYLAND SHALL ISSUE PLEDGES LAWSUIT &mdash; EXISTING OWNERS MAY
        KEEP FIREARMS &mdash; SALES BAN BEGINS JAN 1, 2027 &mdash; CALIFORNIA'S
        IDENTICAL LAW (AB 1127) ALREADY BEING CHALLENGED IN JAYMES V. BONTA
        &mdash; SUBSCRIBE TO BEARING FREEDOM FOR FULL COVERAGE &mdash; SB 334
        PASSES MARYLAND LEGISLATURE 92-39 &mdash; BANS SALE OF GLOCKS AND ALL
        CRUCIFORM TRIGGER BAR PISTOLS &mdash; ON GOVERNOR MOORE'S DESK &mdash;
        MARYLAND SHALL ISSUE PLEDGES LAWSUIT &mdash; EXISTING OWNERS MAY KEEP
        FIREARMS &mdash; SALES BAN BEGINS JAN 1, 2027
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-state">Maryland &mdash; SB 334</div>
        <h1>Maryland Glock Ban</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
          Maryland's legislature passed SB 334, banning the sale of Glocks and
          all pistols with cruciform trigger bars. The bill targets the internal
          mechanism that enables illegal auto-sear "switch" conversion &mdash;
          and bans the most popular handgun in America in the process.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-meta">
          <span class="meta-chip passed">Passed Legislature</span>
          <span class="meta-chip pending">Awaiting Governor</span>
          <span class="meta-chip">Senate 28-16</span>
          <span class="meta-chip">House 92-39</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Stats -->
    <div class="stats" style="margin-left:20px;margin-right:20px;">
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-val red">SB 334</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Bill Number</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-val">92-39</div>
        <div class="stat-label">House Vote</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-val">28-16</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Senate Vote</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-val red">3 yrs</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Max Prison</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-val red">$5,000</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Max Fine</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-val yellow">Jan 2027</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Sales Ban Date</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="content">
      <!-- What the bill does -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="sh">What the bill does</div>
        <p>
          SB 334 creates a new category of prohibited firearm: the <strong
            >"machine gun convertible pistol."</strong
          > It bans the manufacture, sale, purchase, receipt, and transfer of any
          semiautomatic pistol with a <strong>cruciform trigger bar</strong> that
          can be converted to fully automatic fire by installing an illegal auto-sear
          device (commonly called a "Glock switch") to the rear of the slide.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is <strong>not</strong> the Maryland Handgun Roster. SB 334 creates
          an entirely new criminal prohibition in the Criminal Law Article (sections
          4-301, 4-302, 4-305.2, and 4-306). Even guns already approved on the roster
          become illegal to sell if they meet the new definition.
        </p>

        <div class="co co-red">
          <div class="co-t">The cruciform trigger bar is the target</div>
          <p>
            The bill defines a <strong>"cruciform trigger bar"</strong> as a component
            that serves as a link between the trigger and the firing pin, with its
            sear incorporated into a cross-shaped surface. This is the design feature
            that makes "Glock switch" installation possible. Every Glock ever made
            uses this mechanism.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="co co-yellow">
          <div class="co-t">The V Series blocking tab doesn't save you</div>
          <p>
            Glock redesigned its pistols (the "V Series") to resist switch
            installation by adding a blocking tab. SB 334 specifically
            anticipated this: the bill states a gun is still prohibited even if
            it has a "piece of material" designed to block switch attachment, <strong
              >as long as that material can be removed with a common household
              tool</strong
            >. The V Series is banned.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Which guns -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="sh">Which guns are affected</div>

        <table class="tb">
          <tr><th>Manufacturer</th><th>Models</th><th>Status</th></tr>
          <tr
            ><td><strong>Glock (Gen 1-5)</strong></td><td
              >All models (G17, G19, G26, G43, G45, etc.)</td
            ><td class="b-ban">BANNED</td></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><strong>Glock V Series</strong></td><td
              >All V Series models (still uses cruciform trigger bar)</td
            ><td class="b-ban">BANNED</td></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><strong>PSA Dagger</strong></td><td
              >Glock-pattern clone with compatible trigger bar</td
            ><td class="b-ban">BANNED</td></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><strong>Shadow Systems</strong></td><td
              >MR920, DR920, CR920, XR920 (Glock-pattern trigger)</td
            ><td class="b-ban">BANNED</td></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><strong>Polymer80</strong></td><td>Glock-pattern builds</td><td
              class="b-ban">BANNED</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><strong>Hammer-fired pistols</strong></td><td
              >Beretta 92, CZ 75, Sig P226, 1911-pattern</td
            ><td class="b-ok">NOT AFFECTED</td></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><strong>S&W M&P, SIG P320, Springfield XD</strong></td><td
              >Striker-fired but may not use cruciform trigger bar</td
            ><td class="b-warn">TBD &mdash; MSP list pending</td></tr
          >
        </table>

        <div class="co">
          <div class="co-t">Maryland State Police publishes the final list</div>
          <p>
            SB 334 requires the Maryland Department of State Police to adopt
            regulations and <strong
              >publish a list of specifically prohibited pistol models</strong
            > before the sales ban takes effect January 1, 2027. The exact scope beyond
            Glock-pattern guns will be determined administratively &mdash; no further
            legislation required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="co co-red">
          <div class="co-t">The most popular handgun in America</div>
          <p>
            Glock holds approximately 65% of the U.S. law enforcement market and
            roughly 35% of the civilian handgun market. Over 20 million Glock
            pistols have been sold worldwide. Under <em>Heller</em> (2008), arms "in
            common use for lawful purposes" are constitutionally protected.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What bill explicitly excludes -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="sh">What the bill explicitly excludes</div>
        <div class="fl">
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Hammer-fired semiautomatic pistols</strong
            > &mdash; explicitly excluded by the definition
          </div>
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Striker-fired pistols without a cruciform trigger bar</strong
            > that have a trigger bar shielded from interference by a pistol converter
          </div>
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Revolvers</strong
            > &mdash; not semiautomatic, not covered
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Impact on buyers -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="sh">Impact on gun owners &amp; buyers</div>

        <table class="tb">
          <tr><th>Action</th><th>After Jan 1, 2027</th></tr>
          <tr
            ><td>Keep your existing Glock</td><td class="b-ok"
              >Legal &mdash; no confiscation</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td>Buy a new Glock from a dealer</td><td class="b-ban"
              >Prohibited</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td>Buy a used Glock via private sale</td><td class="b-ban"
              >Prohibited</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td>Transfer to immediate family member</td><td class="b-ok"
              >Legal</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr><td>Inherit a Glock</td><td class="b-ok">Legal</td></tr>
          <tr
            ><td>Buy out of state and bring back to MD</td><td class="b-ban"
              >Prohibited (covers "receiving")</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td>Have a dealer repair/service your Glock</td><td class="b-ok"
              >Legal</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td>Sell your Glock to a non-family MD resident</td><td
              class="b-ban">Prohibited</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td>Sell your Glock to an out-of-state buyer via FFL</td><td
              class="b-ok">Legal</td
            ></tr
          >
        </table>

        <div class="co co-red">
          <div class="co-t">Used market effectively killed</div>
          <p>
            With no legal transfer mechanism outside of family and inheritance,
            the used Glock market in Maryland is eliminated. Ownership is
            grandfathered but transferability is not.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Exemptions -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="sh">Exemptions</div>
        <div class="fl">
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Active law enforcement officers</strong
            >
          </div>
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Retired law enforcement officers</strong
            >
          </div>
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Active military members</strong
            >
          </div>
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Licensed dealers</strong
            > for servicing or out-of-state transfers
          </div>
          <div class="fl-i">
            <span class="fl-b" style="background:var(--green)"></span><strong
              >Existing owners</strong
            > &mdash; may keep firearms, transfer to immediate family
